history.content: Most of the projects aren't as big as you would expect. Last semester, we had 3 projects, each of which had two fairly independent parts. Out of these "six" projects, three were basically light homeworks under the name of "project" while the other three were actually involved projects which doesn't make it any different from 61A+B. It is a tough class for most because it presents entirely new concepts that you might not have even seen in high school (unlike 61A+B) but they do provide A TON of resources at your disposal. My advice would be to join last semester's Piazza and look at the resources they have in the Google Drive folder. They have literally split every single exam problem by topic so as soon as you learn a new topic (be it C programming or caching), you have a ton of test questions to help you make sure you actually understood the material. Good luck!
